      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The lack of clarity tactic is a favorite among goblins. They often use vague language or make unsubstantiated claims to create confusion and uncertainty. This can be a red flag, as it may indicate that the email is trying to manipulate or deceive you.\n\nFor example, consider this fake email:\n\n\"Your account has been compromised. Please click on this link to verify your information and prevent further unauthorized access.\"\n\nThis email is vague and doesn't provide any specific details about the alleged compromise or what the link is supposed to do. A goblin might use this tactic to try to get you to click on a malicious link or reveal sensitive information.\n\nTo spot this tactic, your staff should be on the lookout for emails that:\n\n* Use vague or generic language\n* Make unsubstantiated claims or accusations\n* Don't provide specific details or context\n* Ask you to take action without explaining what that action is or why it's necessary\n\nBy being aware of these tactics, your staff can be more vigilant and less likely to fall victim to spear-phishing attacks.",
